      "content": "i know there's help out there, but help doesn't stop the pain. it just manages it, maybe. but it's still there. it's like i'm just enduring a life that i never even asked for. sometimes i look at the silence of things—like when a machine just stops running—and i think there must be a kind of peace in that. just a way to finally be still.",
